cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper deals with visual place recognition using convolutional neural networks.
- cs.RO (Robotics) is also likely as the paper proposes a heuristic policy for robot navigation based on the retrieved closest place.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the paper proposes a novel loss function for learning the concept of distance efficiently.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is relevant as the paper proposes a method for robot navigation based on visual input and machine learning.
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is relevant as the paper deals with omnidirectional cameras and incorporates circular padding and rotation invariance in the network design.
